latestIgtvVideos.title: Much Needed Topic! - Ways to cope up with Stress during the pandemic: 😤
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
•
1.) Try controlled breathing:
Breathe in for 4 seconds.
HOLD the air inside for 4 seconds.
Breathe OUT 4 seconds.
HOLD for 4 seconds.
•
Repeat : may be 4-5 times. (Helps your lungs get stronger and relieve stress + anxiety and helps you to relax.)
•
Next :
Inhale and breathe in for 4 seconds through nose, exhale for 8 seconds through mouth.
•
2.) Follow a daily routine (do things that you enjoy.) + Exercise - Physical activities does wonders for our mental health.
•
3.) Set Limits around news on Covid -19:
Excessively checking updates of corona virus news can leave you stressed. TURN OFF PUSH NOTIFICATIONS FROM news apps!
Celebrating positive stories can Boost your mood and well being!
•
4.) Interacting with animals has shown to decrease levels of cortisol (a stress-related hormone) and lower blood pressure. Other studies have found that pets can reduce loneliness, increase feelings of social support, and boost your mood.
•
PART TWO IS ON THE WAY!!! will be uploaded soon❤️ i hope you are all doing okay. You can do this! Stay Strong. ✨

latestIgtvVideos.title: ⚠️WATCHOUT for these Harmful ingredients when you buy a shampoo! :
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Salon recommended products might have silicone for adding shine. Silicons are NOT extremely toxic/harmful but it builds an extra layer on the hair which may be difficult to remove. It gives a dry feel and dull appearance. You may even notice that your hair becomes weaker and more prone to breakage. And if you're using a form of silicone that isn't water-soluble, it can be really hard to remove it with a regular wash. Make sure you use water soluble silicones.
~
The rest of them mentioned in the video are harmful, which if you use it for the next 3 years, i’m sure that it will result in undesirable hairloss.
~
